description.text:
The Homebuyer Education Workshop provides attendees information about the process it takes to purchase a home through the Down Payment Assistance Program.
The workshop is designed to ensure that all participants receive the necessary information about the home buying process. Some topics covered include credit, budgeting, savings, mortgage loans, house selection, lenders, realtors, home inspection, home maintenance and closing day. There is no cost to attend the workshop. The homebuyer will receive a certificate of completion that is valid for one year after completing the course.
